T1  - Intra-industry specialization: Some observations on concepts and measurement
AU  - Kol, Jacob
AU  - Mennes, Loet B.M.
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 21
IS  - 1
SP  - 173
EP  - 181
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/08/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(86)90013-9
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199686900139
AB  - Recently an index for measuring intra-industry specialization has been proposed by Glejser et al. In the present paper the scope and properties of the Glejser-index are discussed and compared with those of other related measures. From the variety of these measures and their applications, two main areas of analysis emerge: namely the study of (matching) trade flows and of (the similarity of) trade patterns. We indicate which measure would be preferable for each of these two areas.
ER  - 

